Mica for Win32, WPF Sample

The key things are:

1. Make your window inherit from MicaWindow class provided
2. Use Transparent as window background
3. On your WPF window, you must use this WindowChrome config (otherwise, it won't work):

<WindowChrome.WindowChrome>
        <WindowChrome
        CaptionHeight="32"
        ResizeBorderThickness="8"
        CornerRadius="0"
        GlassFrameThickness="-1"
        UseAeroCaptionButtons="True" />
</WindowChrome.WindowChrome>
